<br>
Justing my normal charm tactics, I had SoW on, I tashed my intended pet, pulled it to a place where I could safely charm it, charmed it, went out, got another rat to kill, pulled it to a safe spot, sent in the charmed rat, rooted the target rat, let them beat on each other, nuked once to make sure I'd get xp too, and watched my pet beat up the other rat.  Sounds simple enough, and it worked fairly well.  <br>
<br>
Charm broke a bit more than I'd perfer so I had to run to a safe distance and recharm a few times in the battle, but I did manage to slay that rat.  The problem I ran into was where I would normally break the charm and nuke my former pet into oblivion to get xp for him too, he regenned too fast after I broke the charm for me to slay him.  Logically, this means I should just root him and grab another pet to finish the job, but in this particular case, he managed to resist my root and chased me all the way to the zone out.  *sighs*<br>
<br>
With a big rash of guild hunts and events, I haven't had a chance to try charm soloing again in the planes.  Now that they are slowing down a bit, I am looking back into it so I can continue pushing hard on my way to KEI. (just a personal goal of mine)<br>
<br>
So I just wanted to hear from other charmers out there to see if I should adjust my tactics a bit in the planes any, if there are any recommended places to charm kite in Tier 1, and if there is any other advice you would give a 54 Illusionist.  Any and all comments are welcome. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trump13>Trump13</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/2/03 11:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charm Kiting in the Planes...need advice</span><hr size=1> That happens in disease too?<br>
<br>
Well, here's what happens in Nightmare.  When the creature gets low on health (usually about 1/2 - 3/4 a bubble left or so) it will try and run away.  However, if the person (or pet) who is highest on the aggro list is not in melee range (or close to it) the creature will regen as if it is not engaged at all.  Like about 25% regen in one tick.  So, if you are going to break charm with your pet at VERY low health (you're sure itis going to run) stand next to it.  Also, if it is rooted it won't regen because its not running.<br>
<br>
So generally, yeah, I just get a new pet hehe.<br>
<br>
I tend to solo in nightmare in my free time because its easy to find things to kill.  Also, there is a fairly decent amount of space to run around in circles to build up some space (I usually just use run3 and don't get SoW).  Also there are some static spawn scattered around for easy killing.  I haste my pet, and then slow the enemy, and I can usually get 4 or 5 kills before needing to kill my pet.  If charm breaks sooner I'll switch out sometimes too just because its not worth it to recharm something at 1/2 life hehe.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
